CHANGELOG
=========

All notable changes to the Shell Unit Test Framework will be documented in this file.

## [1.0.0] - 2025-10-27

### Added
- Initial release of Shell Unit Test Framework
- Cross-platform support for Linux and macOS
- Automatic OS detection and GNU tools validation
- Rich assertion library:
  * assert_equals - Test value equality
  * assert_contains - Test string containment
  * assert_file_contains - Test file content
  * assert_file_not_contains - Test file content absence
  * assert_file_exists - Test file existence
  * assert_success - Test command success
  * assert_exit_code - Test specific exit codes
- Multiple output formats:
  * Console output with colors (default)
  * JSON format
  * YAML format
  * CSV format
  * JUnit XML format
- Test result recording and tracking
- Performance timing with millisecond precision
- Quiet mode for CI/CD integration
- Command-line options:
  * --format for output format selection
  * --output for custom output file
  * --quiet for suppressing console output
- Environment variable support:
  * TEST_OUTPUT_FORMAT
  * TEST_QUIET_MODE
- Comprehensive documentation
- Installation guide
- Usage examples

### Features
- Colored console output for better readability
- Automatic output filename generation
- Test suite organization with headers and sections
- Detailed error messages with context
- Exit code handling for CI/CD systems
- JSON escaping for safe output
- XML escaping for JUnit format
- Timestamp support in ISO 8601 format
- Epoch millisecond timing for performance measurement

### Platform Support
- macOS (Darwin) with GNU tools detection
- Linux with standard tools
- Automatic fallback for GNU utilities on macOS
- Cross-platform path handling

### Documentation
- Complete README with examples
- Installation instructions (INSTALL)
- API reference
- Best practices guide
- Troubleshooting section
- Platform-specific notes

